{
  "local_port": 36786,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get call history for my Airtel prepaid number?",
  "response": "To get the call history for your Airtel prepaid number, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Airtel Thanks App:**\n   - Download and install the Airtel Thanks app from the Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n   - Log in using your Airtel number and OTP (One-Time Password).\n   - Go to the \"Usage Details\" or \"Call History\" section within the app. Here, you can view your call history, including call duration and numbers dialed.\n\n2. **Airtel Website:**\n   - Visit the Airtel website ([www.airtel.in](https://www.airtel.in)).\n   - Click on \"Login\" and enter your Airtel number.\n   - After logging in, navigate to the \"Usage Details\" or similar section where you can access your call history.\n\n3. **Customer Care:**\n   - You can also call Airtel customer care at 121 or 198 from your Airtel number.\n   - Follow the IVR (Interactive Voice Response) prompts to reach the section where you can request your call history. You may need to speak to a customer service representative who can assist you with this.\n\n4. **SMS:**\n   - You can send an SMS with the text \"CALL\" to 121. You may receive a response with details on how to access your call history or be prompted to call customer care for further assistance.\n\nPlease note that Airtel may have specific policies and limitations on how far back you can retrieve call history, and some methods might require you to provide additional verification for security purposes.",
